amuse.scheduler.gui.navigation
Interface BackButtonUsable

All Known Implementing Classes:
JPanelSettings
public interface BackButtonUsable

This interface is used in combination with JPanelAmuseNavigator to allow certain JPanels in the Wizard to have different "Back" button behavior.

Author:
Clemens Waeltken

Method Summary
 boolean backButtonClicked()
          This method should delegate the event to the current component displayed by the AmuseNavigator and trigger the correct behavior.
 java.lang.String getBackButtonText()
          This method should return the text to be displayed on the "Back" button.
 

Method Detail

backButtonClicked

boolean backButtonClicked()
This method should delegate the event to the current component displayed by the AmuseNavigator and trigger the correct behavior.

Returns:
Return true if you want the navigator to trigger it's default behavior.

getBackButtonText

java.lang.String getBackButtonText()
This method should return the text to be displayed on the "Back" button.

Returns:
- String containing the button text to be displayed in the AmuseNavigator.
